plored cases, except for the\npropagation in the hotter loop. For a cool, low-density initial coronal loop,\nthe post-shock plasma ahead of upward chromospheric flows might explain at\nleast part of the observed correspondence between type II spicules and EUV\nemission excess.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 9 May 2014 10:26:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-05"}
